To make sure it’s universally readable, you could add three last touches:

```css
/* Extra accessibility refinements */
:focus-visible {
  outline: 3px solid #005577;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* High‑contrast mode support */
@media (prefers-contrast: more) {
  body { background-color: #fff; color: #000; }
  section { background: #fff; border: 2px solid #000; }
  a { color: #0000EE; }
}

/* Dark‑mode alternative */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  body { background-color: #121212; color: #f2f2f2; }
  section { background-color: #1e1e1e; }
  a { color: #9dcbe2; }
  footer { color: #aaa; }
}
```

Those additions let browsers automatically switch contrast or color schemes based on user settings and give visible focus outlines for keyboard navigation.

